u.seg: life_story finished send ‎‎Story told by John Kaloros in 1988.

spanGrp.span: As for us, the time of independence, there was the National Party group,
there was the UCNH group (Union des Communautés des Nouvelles Hebrides).
119-001 Taos komam sup̃ ni independen , ipiatlak krup ni
Nasonal Pati , § 119-002 ipiatlak krup ni UCNH .
The UCNH was two Parties. One was against independence and one was for independence.
§ 119-003 UCNH gar rapi Pati inru . Go
kaaru ikenski independen , kaaru imuur independen .
But their policy was for independence
But the UCNH wanted independence in
§ 119-005 Me namroan ni UCNH imuurin na ifla pi ntau kemer lim go
tukfo mai sat independen , me Nasonal Pati , § 119-006 ga imuurin na .
(KK) The UCNH wanted the two governments to develop more.
UCNH ga imuurin na taos kafman ranru rakmer nrus defelopki .
And to build the country to make it come up. And schooling should also grow.
§ 119-008 Go rakmer tfag na nfanu kenrus pak
elag . Go skul me keta nrus pa .
But the National Party said, "It's enough. Let it be today, let it be today." That is the one who is against us. But I was in the UCNH, and some were in the National Party.
Me kineu ato UCNH me tete ruto Nasonal Pati komam telaap §
(KK) At Erakor. But we didn't say it was bad. We said it is good,
we leave the two governments to keep giving us education, that it should keep going.
Utli iwi , § 119-012 tukta tao kafman ranru
rakta tu kit edukesen keta lakor pa .
But when we hurried, they were on guard and we couldn't do anything about it.
§ 119-013 Me selwan tuknrogtor , rakmuti go akit tukano preg namrun .
But the white people have good knowledge.
§ 119-014 Me nam̃er taar rupiatlak ntaewen nen kin iwi .
They always want to help us, but we don't want it, we chase them away, they go. But they would take us, they hold us in their hands.
§ 119-015 Rumuurin na rukwelu ser mal akit tumalkir , tukpasir
rupa . Me gar ruslatsok akit tutau naarur tau .
White people have good knowledge, and they don't get angry. They want to help everyone.
§ 119-017 Nam̃er taar rupiatlak na ntaewen nen iwi ,
go nmaeto itiikir . Rumuur rukwelu ser naat .
It is a good way that we can look at and know.
§ 119-018 Go ipi sup̃ wi nen kin , komam me kolemsi go kotae .
And the thinking then, for us who were in the other Party, we didn't want to do harm to white people.
§ 119-019 Go namroan nen kin ito komam tenakon nen uto Pati kaaru , uta muurin na kofregsaki kano taar mau .
Because our blood is just one blood.
§ 119-020 Nlaken akit nrakit ga iskei m̃as .
But the other one, they wanted to harm their friends, white people, they made a mistake.
§ 119-021 Me tekaaru rumuurin na rukfregsaki asler , nam̃er taar rupreg
mistek . E , tete nakrakpelwen , taos nakrakpelwen mistek .
If you made a small mistake they would chase you out, deport you.
That's a bad way, the way that we in the UCNH
like, the UMP we saw that it wasn't good.
§ 119-023 Tenen ipi sup̃ sa , tenen kin komam nanre ni
UCNH , § 119-024 taos UMP uleka na itap wi mau .
If you give people time they can have a good education.
§ 119-025 Natam̃ol p̃atua mal go ga ipiatlak educated wi .
You give some time so he can tell you what you have done wrong.
§ 119-026 P̃atua mal nen kin ga itae nriki ki nafte kin ag kusrafwes .
You are wrong there, you took the wrong road.
§ 119-027 Kurogwes taosi kurog kusraf , a , kusraf napu kia .
He knows, the white man knows how to teach you, because he has lots of education in his head.
§ 119-028 Ga itae , kano taar itae tafnau ag , nlaken ga ipiatlak education p̃ur ito np̃aun .
We black people we think that we know alot, but it's not so.
§ 119-029 Akit nam̃er got tumroki na , tuipe tae itop me itiik .
You go on and on, but you miss the road.
§ 119-030 Kupanpanpan kusursap̃ napu , yu mestem rod , kusursap̃ napu .
Ok, now you will go back.
So he could advise you again, see? It's not good that we rush. It is not good that we hurry.
§ 119-032 Blong hem i advaesem yu bakegen
yu luk ? I nogud yumi hariap
